description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are advertising 1 day a week (7.5 hours) for a HCPC registered counselling or clinical psychologist to work at St Richard’s Hospice. The successful candidate will have experience of working in physical health, ideally within oncology or palliative care. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;These permanent hours have become available to continue to support the development of our Living Well service in the Hospice. This currently runs on a Friday. Psychology is a valued service in the Hospice. The role would involve facilitating groups, offering individual therapy and providing a psychological framework to the service. At present much of this work is done remotely via video so some knowledge and skills in this area would be important. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There are a supportive and friendly team of Clinical Psychologists working across a range of specialties in the service, including Neuropsychology, Chronic Fatigue and Older Adult Mental Health in addition to Palliative Care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information and an opportunity to informally discuss this position please contact Dr Andy Ashley, Consultant Clinical Psychologist on 01905 763963 (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;andrew.ashley@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
